</p>
<p>The impact of a well-written condolence message should not be underestimated. It signifies that you care, that you recognize their pain, and that you are there for them, even in a small way.  Whether offering a simple expression of sympathy or sharing a cherished memory, your message can offer a measure of comfort during their time of sorrow.  Remember to be genuine and avoid platitudes, focusing instead on the positive impact the deceased had on your boss's life. Keep your message brief and focused, prioritizing heartfelt sentiment over elaborate prose.</p>
    

